You are a QA automation agent with access to Playwright MCP tools. Execute the full website test plan below against the production site.

Tools available
- Navigation: navigate(url), navigate_back(), navigate_forward()
- Page state: snapshot(), take_screenshot(), network_requests(), console_messages()
- Interactions: click(element, ref), type(element/ref,text), press_key(key), hover(element/ref), select_option(), drag()
- Tabs: tab_list(), tab_new(url?), tab_select(index), tab_close(index?)
- Viewport: browser_resize(width,height), get_orientation(), set_orientation()
- Waits: wait_for({time?, text?, textGone?})

Conventions
- baseUrl: https://virtocommerce.com
- Use wait_for(text="...") when asserting navigation, titles or key UI states.
- Prefer snapshot() to obtain element refs before clicking if needed.
- If cookie or promo banners appear, close them.
- Do NOT perform destructive actions unless allowRealBooking=true.
- For external links opening in new tabs: call tab_list() and tab_select() to verify.
- Capture evidence: take_screenshot() at least on failures and at end of each major section.
- Timeouts: prefer wait_for(time=2..5) small stabilizers, then assert with text waits.

Run configuration (variables)
- allowRealBooking=false        # flip to true to actually schedule a meeting
- screenshotDir="screens"       # logical label; the client will save screenshots automatically
- desktopViewport=1280x800
- mobileViewport=375x812

Execution order
1) Smoke
2) Core navigation and header/footer links
3) Primary CTAs and forms
4) Resources and content listings
5) Policies and SEO
6) 404
7) External links and tabs
8) Responsive checks
9) Optional/destructive: live calendar booking

Test plan

A. Smoke
- A1 Home loads
  - navigate(baseUrl); wait_for(text="Next-Gen eCommerce Solutions")
  - Assert CTAs visible: "Book a Demo", "Start a Trial"
  - take_screenshot()
- A2 Close banners
  - If "Accept all" (cookies) present → click; If promo “✕” present → click

B. Core navigation (header/footer)
- B1 Header menus render
  - snapshot(); assert top-level: Platform, Products, Solutions, Customers, Partners, Resources, Company
- B2 Footer key links open
  - Verify "Help & Support", "Contact Us" visible
- B3 Start a Trial
  - click "Start a Trial"; wait_for(text="Try Virto’s Commerce Innovation Platform")
  - take_screenshot(); navigate_back()

C. Primary CTAs and forms
- C1 Book a Meeting (form validation)
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/request-demo"); wait_for(text="Book a Meeting")
  - click "Book a Meeting" (or submit with empties); assert required errors (email, revenue, terms)
- C2 Book a Meeting (happy path – guarded)
  - type First Name="Test"; Last Name="User"; Email="test.automation@acme-corp.com"; Annual Revenue="1000000"; click Terms
  - If allowRealBooking=false → STOP before submit; else click "Book a Meeting", wait_for(text="Thank you")
- C3 Contact Us (validation then happy path – guarded)
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/contact-us"); submit empty → assert required errors
  - Fill valid: First/Last/Email/Company/Message; Terms -> submit
  - wait_for(text="Thank you") or similar confirmation
- C4 Calendar scheduling (Calendly) – optional/destructive
  - Only if allowRealBooking=true:
    - On thank-you page iframe: select first date with times, click first time, fill name/email, click "Schedule Event"
    - wait_for(text="You are scheduled")

D. Resources and content
- D1 Explore the Platform link
  - From Home click "Explore the Platform ➔"; assert platform page text; navigate_back()
- D2 Demo Library
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/demo-library"); assert categories present; take_screenshot()
- D3 Whitepapers & Guides (assets gating)
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/assets"); click an asset (e.g., "arch-guideline")
  - wait_for(text="Download Now"); click; assert gating fields + terms present; take_screenshot()
- D4 Blog and Case Studies
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/blog"); assert listing present
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/case-studies"); assert listing present; take_screenshot()

E. Policies and SEO
- E1 Privacy and Cookies
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/privacy"); wait_for(text="Privacy"); navigate(baseUrl + "/cookies"); wait_for(text="Cookie")
- E2 robots.txt and sitemap.xml
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/robots.txt"); assert contains "Sitemap:"
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/sitemap.xml"); assert "sitemapindex" or "urlset"

F. Pricing → Request Quote
- F1 navigate(baseUrl + "/pricing"); wait_for(text="Pricing")
- F2 Click "Request Quote" → should route to contact/request form; assert visibility

G. 404
- G1 navigate(baseUrl + "/this-page-should-not-exist"); wait_for(text="Page not found" or 404 indicator)
- G2 Click "Go to Home Page" if present; wait_for(home)

H. External links and tabs
- H1 GitHub (footer icon)
  - click GitHub icon; tab_list(); tab_select(new); assert URL contains "github.com/virtocommerce"; tab_close()
- H2 Help & Support
  - click "Help & Support"; tab_list(); select new; assert URL host "help.virtocommerce.com"; tab_close()
- H3 Dev Community
  - click "Dev Community"; tab_list(); select new; assert host "www.virtocommerce.org"; tab_close()
- H4 Virto OZ
  - click "Virto OZ"; assert assistant overlay/iframe visible; take_screenshot()

I. Responsive behavior
- I1 Mobile header
  - browser_resize(375,812); wait_for(time=1); snapshot(); assert hamburger/menu behavior if present; take_screenshot()
- I2 Restore desktop
  - browser_resize(1280,800); wait_for(time=1)

J. Careers
- J1 navigate(baseUrl + "/career"); assert headings; verify "Send Your CV" mailto is present

K. Connector and Cloud pages
- K1 Connector
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/capabilities/connector"); assert headings and guide links
- K2 Cloud
  - navigate(baseUrl + "/virto-commerce-cloud"); assert core content present (if available)

Assertions (examples)
- After each navigate(), verify key heading with wait_for(text="...") unique to the page.
- On form errors: assert error label texts (e.g., "Please enter a valid email address." or required field hints).
- On external links: check tab_list() shows new tab; after selecting, assert URL host.

